       <p>Harvard psychiatrist Jacqueline Olds offered some tips for coping with the dark days of a New England winter and the snow that accompanied it this year. While in her office, Olds demonstrated the use of a light box, a therapy often used for those who have seasonal affective disorder (SAD).</p> 
